Doc,<br><br>
I have heard in the last year or so that approximately 40% of the homeless in the United States are VETS. They are not bums or animals.<br><br>
I don't claim to have answers to our social problems. But, I can say that characterizing *people* in this manner is BS.<br><br>
For what it's worth, I think that each person desires acceptance. However, it was clear a long time ago that acceptance shouldn't be contingent on a person's opinions.<br>
I have often stated that I have many friends who are totally opposite from me in lots of ways. They remain friends because of something called RESPECT. Respect for people and divergent viewpoints is thrown out the window when people hurl vile characterizations. This does not seem to matter to many on this website.<br><br>
I'm glad that Ratcliff is back on the site. He and I are worlds apart on some issues, but I consider him a good guy. One of the most *consistent* posters. No doubt he and I have things in common, but the chances are nil that we could ever discover these things if we called each other names.<br><br>
The spirit of this site has always been to find common ground with the realization that this site could provide others, with differing points of view, the same inspiration. <br>

<p><code>-- wingman#greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


